M. catonis. M. Porcius Cato, the Censor, consul 13.c. 195, sur- named Sapiens, was born of plebeian family about B.c. 234, and served with distinction through the Second Punic XVar. He is the principal character in Cicero’s dialogue ‘de seneetute,' and is chosen by Horace as a typical example of the old Roman Simplicity and austerity in an age which was fast becoming enervated by corruption and luxury. (Hor. 2 Od. xv. 11.)
